                        <h3>What is the difference between khula and talaq?</h3>
                        <p><strong>Khula is wife-initiated</strong> (court decree, dower usually returned). <strong>Talaq
                                is husband-initiated</strong> (Union Council notice, dower paid). Khula takes 3 to 18
                            months. Talaq takes 90 days from notice. Neither needs the other spouse's consent.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Can I speak to a female divorce lawyer about my case?</h3>
                        <p>Yes. Advocate Reema Jawed is a <strong>lady advocate</strong> who handles your case herself.
